Analysis
Comparison of Methods
Bag of Words is simple and computationally efficient but does not
capture contextual meaning. TF-IDF improves performance by assigning
importance to words, leading to better accuracy.
Performance Analysis
TF-IDF achieved better accuracy than Bag of Words due to its ability to
reduce the impact of common words. The performance is significantly
improved when using larger datasets such as IMDB.
Time Complexity
Bag of Words is faster since it only counts word frequencies. TF-IDF
takes slightly more time due to additional weighting calculations.
Trade-offs
There is a trade-off between performance and computational
complexity:
BoW → Fast but less accurate
TF-IDF → Better accuracy with moderate time
Advanced models → Highest accuracy but high computational cost
Conclusion
From this experiment, it can be concluded that TF-IDF provides better
performance than Bag of Words while maintaining reasonable
computational cost. Advanced models offer superior accuracy but
require more resources. Therefore, the choice of method depends on the
application requirements.
